      "note_no": "43",
      "note": "The epithet 'azim (\"tremendous\" or \"mighty\") renders it improbable that this sacrifice refers to nothing but the ram which Abraham subsequently found and slaughtered in Ishmael's stead (Genesis xxit, 13). To my mind, the sacrifice spoken of here is the one repeated every year by countless believers in connection with the pilgrimage to Mecca (al-hajj), which, in itself, commemorates the experience of Abraham and Ishmael and constitutes one of the \"five pillars\" of Islam. (See 22:27-37, as well as 2:196-203.)"
